# Placeholder for the four ingest secrets. Once sops-nix is wired
# into luna, copy this to `secrets/ingest.env` and `sops -e -i` it so
# the age key encrypts the values in place. Four expected keys:
#
#   OPENWEBUI_API_TOKEN   — generated in Open WebUI UI → Settings → Account
#   ATLASSIAN_EMAIL       — email for Atlassian Cloud basic auth
#   ATLASSIAN_API_TOKEN   — https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens
#   GITHUB_API_TOKEN      — https://github.com/settings/tokens (fine-grained
#                           PAT with repo + issues read on the repos in
#                           `local.ingest.sources.github.repos` AND the
#                           vault repo referenced by the obsidian source.)
#
# The NixOS module consumes each value from a separate *file path*
# (tokenFile / emailFile) rather than env vars, so when you wire up
# sops-nix, split this into four single-line secret files using:
#
#   sops.secrets.openwebui-api-token = {
#     format = "binary";
#     sopsFile = ../../secrets/openwebui-api-token;
#     owner = "ingest";
#     mode = "0400";
#   };
#   sops.secrets.atlassian-email     = { ... sopsFile = ../../secrets/atlassian-email; ... };
#   sops.secrets.atlassian-api-token = { ... sopsFile = ../../secrets/atlassian-api-token; ... };
#   sops.secrets.github-api-token    = { ... sopsFile = ../../secrets/github-api-token; ... };
#
# and reference their `.path` values from luna's `local.ingest` block.
OPENWEBUI_API_TOKEN=REPLACE_ME
ATLASSIAN_EMAIL=REPLACE_ME
ATLASSIAN_API_TOKEN=REPLACE_ME
GITHUB_API_TOKEN=REPLACE_ME
